k/ |title=Freud Museum, Maresfield Gardens, London}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.kansasmemory.org/locate.php?query=Freud |title=Freud, Sigmund and Anna Collection available on Kansas Memory}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.psychiatrie-und-ethik.de/infc/1_gesamt_en.html |title=International Network of Freud Critics}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.ipa.org.uk/ |title=International Psychoanalytical Association}} (founded by Freud in 1910)\n* {{cite book|url=http://bsf.spp.asso.fr/index.php?lvl=notice_display&id=75420|title=Library Catalog of the Pshchoanalytical Association of Paris|language=fr|year=1994|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190501172142/http://bsf.spp.asso.fr/index.php?lvl=notice_display&id=75420|archive-date= May 1, 2019|url-status=live|isbn=9782130465768|publisher=Presses Universitaires de France}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.bartleby.com/people/Freud.html|title= Sigmund Freud Collection|website=Bartleby.com}} (15 works in English)\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.thecjc.org/pdf/sf_biblio.pdf |title=Bibliography of Sigmund Freud's writings|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402181118/http://www.thecjc.org/pdf/sf_biblio.pdf|archive-date=2 April 2019}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/ayounggirlsdiar00freugoog |title=''A Young Girl's Diary''|year=1921|publisher=T. Seltzer}} probably by [[Hermine Hug-Hellmuth]], prefaced with a letter from Freud dated 27 April 1915\n* {{cite web|url=http://jewishhistorylectures.org/2015/03/12/who-was-sigmund-freud-jewish-biography-as-history/|title= Who Was Sigmund Freud?|author=Dr. Henry Abramson|author-link= Henry Abramson|date= 12 March 2015}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.shapell.org/Collection/Jewish-Figures/Freud-Sigmund/|title= Sigmund Freud Personal Manuscripts}}\n* {{PM20|FID=pe/005549}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Patrick Hastings]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of People on the Cover of Time Magazine: 1920s|Cover of ''Time'' Magazine]]\n|years=27 October 1924}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Thomas Lipton]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=Leopold Ziegler}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Goethe Prize]]\n|years=1930}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Ricarda Huch]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Sigmund Freud|state=expanded}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list=\n{{Human psychological development}}\n{{Memory}}\n{{Psychology}}\n{{Psychiatry}}\n{{Criticism of religion}}\n{{Lucian Freud}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n<!--\nPlease do not include categories identifying Freud as a psychiatrist or a psychologist. Despite a popular misconception to the contrary, Freud was not a psychiatrist, and psychology was not his profession. Reliable sources identify Freud as a neurologist or a psychoanalyst; see for instance Arthur S. Reber and Emily Reber's The Penguin Dictionary of Psychology.\n-->\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Freud, Sigmund}}\n[[Category:Sigmund Freud| ]]\n[[Category:1856 births]]\n[[Category:1939 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from P\u0159\u00edbor]]\n[[Category:People from the Margraviate of Moravia]]\n[[Category:19th-century Austrian writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Austrian writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Austrian physicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Austrian physicians]]\n[[Category:Academics and writers on narcissism]]\n[[Category:Austrian atheists]]\n[[Category:Austrian emigrants to England]]\n[[Category:Jewish emigrants from Austria after the Anschluss]]\n[[Category:Austrian people of Ukrainian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Austrian psychoanalysts]]\n[[Category:Jewish psychoanalysts]]\n[[Category:Austrian male writers]]\n[[Category:Deaths by euthanasia]]\n[[Category:Foreign Members of the Royal Society]]\n[[Category:History of psychiatry]]\n[[Category:Jewish atheists]]\n[[Category:Jewish emigrants from Nazi Germany to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Austrian atheist writers]]\n[[Category:People of Galician-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Austrian neurologists]]\n[[Category:Golders Green Crematorium]]\n[[Category:Critics of religions]]\n[[Category:Freud family|Sigmund]]\n[[Category:Members of the Vienna Psychoanalytic Society]]