{"title_page": "List of heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=April 2017}}\n\nThere are a small number of '''[[heritage railway]]s in the [[Republic of Ireland]]''', reflecting [[Ireland]]'s long [[history of rail transport in Ireland|history of rail transport]].  Some former operations have closed, and aspirant operations may have museums and even rolling stock, but no operating track.\n\n==Heritage railways==\nSome of the main preserved or restored railways include:\n* [[Stradbally Woodland Railway]], [[County Laois]]\n* [[Cavan and Leitrim Railway]], [[County Leitrim]]\n* [[Fintown railway station|Fintown Railway]], based in [[Fintown]], it runs along the length of [[Lough Finn]] to [[Glenties]] Line for about a mile\n* [[Lartigue Monorail#Listowel and Ballybunion Railway|Listowel and Ballybunion Railway]], a section of the [[Lartigue Monorail]] system has been restored for visitors in [[Listowel]]\n* [[Waterford and Suir Valley Railway]], running a [[narrow gauge railway]] for 10km from Kilmeaden Station, along the former mainline route from [[Waterford]] to [[Mallow, County Cork|Mallow]] operating alongside the recently opened Deise Greenway\n* [[West Clare Railway]], beginning in [[Ennis]]\n\nwhile former operations included:\n* [[Clonmacnoise and West Offaly Railway]] in [[County Offaly]], run by [[Bord na M\u00f3na]], near [[Shannonbridge]], closed 2008\n* [[Tralee and Dingle Light Railway]], between [[Tralee]] and [[Dingle]], not in operation, since 2013\n\nand aspirant operations, with plans for operating track, include:\n* [[County Donegal Railways Joint Committee]], commemorated by the [[Donegal Railway Centre]] in [[County Donegal]], which once had two [[narrow gauge railway]] systems\n* [[Sligo, Leitrim and Northern Counties Railway]], the last surviving independently operated railway in the Republic of Ireland (1879-1959)\n\n==Preservation groups==\nPreservation groups in Ireland include:\n* [[Railway Preservation Society of Ireland]], based in [[Whitehead, County Antrim|Whitehead]], [[County Antrim]] in [[Northern Ireland]], runs railtours on the [[Dublin-Rosslare railway line]] with \"Sea-Breeze\" trains, along with Santa specials between Dublin and Maynooth in December. Some restoration work is carried out in the Dublin area and at [[Mullingar]].\n* [[Irish Traction Group]], based in [[Carrick-on-Suir]], [[County Tipperary]], has a diesel locomotive collection at the site by the [[Limerick]]&ndash;[[Waterford]] [[rail transport in Ireland|railway route]]. ITG also run regular railtours around the country, sometimes with older (but still in regular use), [[Iarnr\u00f3d \u00c9ireann]] locomotives and rolling stock.\n* [[Irish Steam Preservation Society]], based in [[Stradbally]], [[County Laois]]. Operates the [[Stradbally#Stradbally Woodland Railway|Stradbally Woodland Railway]] with vintage steam and diesel locomotives.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Trains}}\n\n* [[Conservation in the Republic of Ireland]]\n* [[List of heritage railways]]\n* [[List of heritage railways in Northern Ireland]]\n* [[List of narrow gauge railways in Ireland]]\n\n{{Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of heritage railways|Ireland, the Republic of]]\n[[Category:Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland|*]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland-related lists|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Irish railway-related lists|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in Ireland|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Cultural heritage of Ireland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}}\n{{Use Irish English|date=April 2017}}\n\nThere are a small number of '''[[heritage railway]]s in the [[Republic of Ireland]]''', reflecting [[Ireland]]'s long [[history of rail transport in Ireland|history of rail transport]].  Some former operations have closed, and aspirant operations may have museums and even rolling stock, but no operating track.\n\n==Heritage railways==\nSome of the main preserved or restored railways include:\n* [[Stradbally Woodland Railway]], [[County Laois]]\n* [[Cavan and Leitrim Railway]], [[County Leitrim]]\n* [[Fintown railway station|Fintown Railway]], based in [[Fintown]], it runs along the length of [[Lough Finn]] to [[Glenties]] Line for about a mile\n* [[Lartigue Monorail#Listowel and Ballybunion Railway|Listowel and Ballybunion Railway]], a section of the [[Lartigue Monorail]] system has been restored for visitors in [[Listowel]]\n* [[Waterford & Suir Valley Railway]], running a [[narrow gauge railway]] for 10km from Kilmeaden Station, along the former mainline route from [[Waterford]] to [[Mallow, County Cork|Mallow]] operating alongside the recently opened Deise Greenway\n* [[West Clare Railway]], beginning in [[Ennis]]\n\nwhile former operations included:\n* [[Clonmacnoise and West Offaly Railway]] in [[County Offaly]], run by [[Bord na M\u00f3na]], near [[Shannonbridge]], closed 2008\n* [[Tralee and Dingle Light Railway]], between [[Tralee]] and [[Dingle]], not in operation, since 2013\n\nand aspirant operations, with plans for operating track, include:\n* [[County Donegal Railways Joint Committee]], commemorated by the [[Donegal Railway Centre]] in [[County Donegal]], which once had two [[narrow gauge railway]] systems\n* [[Sligo, Leitrim and Northern Counties Railway]], the last surviving independently operated railway in the Republic of Ireland (1879-1959)\n\n==Preservation groups==\nPreservation groups in Ireland include:\n* [[Railway Preservation Society of Ireland]], based in [[Whitehead, County Antrim|Whitehead]], [[County Antrim]] in [[Northern Ireland]], runs railtours on the [[Dublin-Rosslare railway line]] with \"Sea-Breeze\" trains, along with Santa specials between Dublin and Maynooth in December. Some restoration work is carried out in the Dublin area and at [[Mullingar]].\n* [[Irish Traction Group]], based in [[Carrick-on-Suir]], [[County Tipperary]], has a diesel locomotive collection at the site by the [[Limerick]]&ndash;[[Waterford]] [[rail transport in Ireland|railway route]]. ITG also run regular railtours around the country, sometimes with older (but still in regular use), [[Iarnr\u00f3d \u00c9ireann]] locomotives and rolling stock.\n* [[Irish Steam Preservation Society]], based in [[Stradbally]], [[County Laois]]. Operates the [[Stradbally#Stradbally Woodland Railway|Stradbally Woodland Railway]] with vintage steam and diesel locomotives.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Trains}}\n\n* [[Conservation in the Republic of Ireland]]\n* [[List of heritage railways]]\n* [[List of heritage railways in Northern Ireland]]\n* [[List of narrow gauge railways in Ireland]]\n\n{{Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of heritage railways|Ireland, the Republic of]]\n[[Category:Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland|*]]\n[[Category:Republic of Ireland-related lists|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Irish railway-related lists|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in Ireland|Heritage railways in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Cultural heritage of Ireland]]\n", "name_user": "Slambo", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHeritage railways:fix link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_heritage_railways_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland"}
{"title_page": "Thadam", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film directed by Magizh Thirumeni}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Thadam\n| image          = Thadam poster.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Magizh Thirumeni]]\n| producer       = Inder Kumar\n| writer         = Magizh Thirumeni\n| starring       = [[Arun Vijay]]<br>[[Tanya Hope]]<br>[[Smruthi Venkat]]<br>[[Vidya Pradeep]]\n| music          = Arun Raj\n| cinematography = Gopinath\n| editing        = [[N. B. Srikanth]]\n| studio         = Redhan \u2013 The Cinema People\n| distributor    = Screen Scene Media Entertainment \n| released       = 1 March 2019\n| runtime        = 138 Minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RedhanCinemas/status/1029615212318486528|title=#Redhan on Twitter: \"With utmost pleasure and gratitude presenting you the #censor #certificate for #Thadam #releasingsoon #watchout4Thadam #RedhanProduction2\"|website=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n| gross          = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n}}\n\n'''''Thadam''''' ({{Literal translation|Path}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/thadam-movie-review-audience-is-in-awe-of-the-action-thriller-starring-arun-vijay-read-tweets/374775|title=Thadam Movie Review: Audience is in awe of the action thriller starring Arun Vijay - read tweets|website=[[Times Now]]|date=1 March 2019}}</ref> written and directed by [[Magizh Thirumeni]] and produced by Inder Kumar. The film stars [[Arun Vijay]] in a [[double role]] along with [[Tanya Hope]], [[Smruthi Venkat]], and [[Vidya Pradeep]] in the lead roles. The music was composed by Arun Raj, with cinematography done by Gopinath and editing by [[N. B. Srikanth]]. ''Thadam'' marks the Tamil debut of Hope and the film debut of Venkat.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/jun/12/arun-vijays-next-confirmed-to-have-three-heroines-1615878.html</ref> \n\nThe film revolves around two lookalike men, Ezhil and Kavin. While Ezhil is a construction businessman leading a peaceful life, Kavin is a thief who spends most of time gambling and conning. One night, when both are having a hard time, one of them breaks into a man's house and brutally kills him. When the investigation begins, an evidence leads to the cops capturing Ezhil, before they also come across Kavin and find themselves looking for the real murderer among the two as they dig deeper into the investigation.\n\n''Thadam'' was released theatrically on 1 March 2019, opening to praise for Arun Vijay's performance and the writing of the title's logo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/thadam-movie-review-ratings-critics-give-thumbs-arun-vijay-starrer-792894|title=Thadam movie review and ratings: Critics give thumbs up for Arun Vijay-starrer|website=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref> It was commercially successful, becoming one of the highest-grossing films of the year in Tamil Nadu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/thadam-one-of-the-top-4-grossers-in-tamil-nadu-this-year-345259.htm|title=Thadam one of the top 4 grossers in Tamil Nadu this year|website=[[In.com]]|accessdate=17 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/pichaikaran-to-thadam-five-blockbuster-tamil-films-which-were-released-in-the-month-of-march/photostory/74794151.cms?picid=74794153|title='Pichaikaran' to 'Thadam': Five blockbuster Tamil films which were released in the month of March|website=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=24 March 2020|quote='Thadam' was an action thriller which was written and directed by Magizh Thirumeni. Arun Vijay played a dual role in the film along with Tanya Hope, Smruthi Venkat and Vidya Pradeep in main roles. The film turned out to be one of the highest-grossing films of the year in Tamil Nadu.}}</ref> The film is being remade in Telugu as ''[[Red (2020 film)|Red]]'' with [[Ram Pothineni]] in the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/oct/28/thadam-telugu-remake-titled-red-15172.html|title=Thadam Telugu remake titled Red|website=[[Cinema Express]]|accessdate=28 October 2019}}</ref> A [[Hindi]]-language remake with [[Sidharth Malhotra]] is also in works.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sidharth-malhotra-to-star-in-hindi-remake-of-tamil-action-thriller-thadam-film-to-release-on-20-november-8116611.html|title=Sidharth Malhotra to star in Hindi remake of Tamil action thriller Thadam; film to release on 20 November|website=[[Firstpost]]|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thadam-be-remade-hindi-siddharth-malhotra-117344|title='Thadam' to be remade in Hindi with Siddharth Malhotra?|website=[[The News Minute]]|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref>It was being remade into bengali as <nowiki>''Red''</nowiki> with most probably shakib khan play the lead role slated to release in july 2020.\n\n<br />\n\n==Plot==\nEzhil is a construction businessman while his lookalike Kavin is a gambling thief who deceives people along with his sidekick Suruli. A girl named Ananthi loves Kavin, unaware of his real identity. One day, Kavin tries to help Suruli pay his debt by extracting money from Ananthi through lies, but she helps him in spite of knowing the truth. After taking the money, Kavin is enraged and so is Ezhil after a party. That night, one of them breaks into the house of a young man named Akash and beats him to death. The next day, Kavin frees Suruli by paying his debt and wins Ananthi's trust by returning her money and telling her the truth. However, as the investigation of Akash's murder proceeds, a selfie clicked by a couple nearby is found with either of Ezhil or Kavin in it. Both Ezhil and Kavin are brought in and investigated without their knowledge of each other's existence. Gopalakrishnan, an inspector who shares an old rivalry with Ezhil, tortures him. Ezhil reveals his car broke down, and a call taxi driver helped him. Kavin, on the other hand, cites various laws to escape torture. Sub-inspector Malarvizhi is assigned to solve the case. She reaches out to Akash's friend and shows him the photograph of Ezhil/Kavin but he refuses to recognize him. She also questions Suruli and tells him not to leave city without permission, but he secretly escapes.\n\nMalarvizhi then learns of the rivalry between Ezhil and Gopalakrishnan. Ezhil helped the latter's daughter elope with her lover, much against her father's wishes. She gets a call from a forensic expert who informs her about a hair sample recovered from the crime scene and how it doesn't match anyone else in Akash's home. At the police station, a restless Ezhil uses an opportunity to escape, but is interrupted by Kavin. The two violently fight, hurting everyone and destroying the station in the process. It is then revealed they're both identical twins after their DNA is found identical. Both Ezhil and Kavin confess about the same; they parted ways when their parents divorced. Kavin went with his mother who used to gamble a lot and one day tried to convince him that she'd give up gambling, but instead committed suicide. Kavin was then taken in by his father but often got into brawls with him and Ezhil. Growing up, Kavin became interested in studying the law but left studies due to his lack of college ethics. One day, when Kavin came home and left in front of Ezhil whose ring for Deepika went missing, Ezhil reported him to the police. The police beat up Kavin who himself told Ezhil to look for the ring in the drawer. Ezhil realized his mistake but Kavin, who came home for a photo of their mother, vowed to seek revenge. \n\nOn the other hand, Gopalakrishnan still wants to frame Ezhil but the call taxi driver who helped Ezhil reveals he was really stuck on the night of murder. Since it also gets proved that Kavin paid Suruli's debt with gambling money he won after playing all night, the case further complicates. The brothers are presented before the court, where the judge acquits both of them in order to prevent the innocent one from suffering the consequences. A disappointed Malazvizhi later calls Akash's friend to inquire about the girl he was infatuated to. Learning it was Deepika, she is shocked. It is finally revealed that Ezhil murdered Akash for drugging, kidnapping and raping Deepika to death, while Kavin found out about akash's death and helped Ezhil by getting arrested and complicating the case. \n\nKavin meets with Ezhil in the highways and says that Malarvizhi can't reopen the case because she created a fake witness to help Ezhil, and could herself get into trouble. Kavin further reveals that he has forever lost all interest in gambling and he's going to marry Ananthi soon. Ezhil hands him over a photograph of them with their mother and tells him he is going to Mumbai, and later to Copenhagen, never to return. Ezhil has sold all of his property in India, and gives 50% share to Kavin as a tribute. A month later, Kavin marries Ananthi, and realises that his lack of trust in his mother, prompted her to kill herself. At the end, one of the investigating officers claims in a documentary shooting that such a case never happened in the past, before someone tells him similar cases did occur in America and some such cases are listed on the screen.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Arun Vijay]] in a dual role as Ezhil and Kavin\n*[[Tanya Hope]] as Deepika, Ezhil's love interest\n*[[Smruthi Venkat]] as Ananthi, an innocent women and Kavin's one-sided lover \n*[[Vidya Pradeep]] as Sub-Inspector Malarvizhi\n*[[Sonia Aggarwal]] as Ezhil and Kavin's mother\n*[[FEFSI Vijayan]] as Inspector M. Gopalakrishnan\n*Yesakkiappan as Aakash\n*[[Yogi Babu]] as Suruli\n*[[George Maryan|George]] as Police Constable Dhanasekar \n*[[Meera Krishnan]] as Chechi \n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIn March 2017, [[Arun Vijay]] revealed that he would next work on a film directed by [[Magizh Thirumeni]], which marks the second film for the duo after ''[[Thadaiyara Thaakka]]'' (2012).<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/yet-another-thriller-for-arun-vijay/articleshow/57631341.cms</ref> Produced by Inder Kumar, the film was launched in April 2017 at Chennai.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/arun-vijay-magizh-thirumeni-untitled-movie-tamil-movie-preview-21475</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/yet-another-thriller-for-arun-vijay/articleshow/57631341.cms</ref> Arun Vijay was reported to be playing a double role, while the film would be based on a real life story.<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/arun-vijay-to-play-dual-role-in-the-film-with-magizh-thirumeni-news-tnpl-reejnugfihhdg.html</ref> The film has three heroines, Tanya Hope, Vidya Pradeep and Smruthi Venkat.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/tanya-hope-soori-and-vidya-pradeep-the-three-heroines-in-arun-vijay-magizh-tirumeni-thadam-tamil-news-191506</ref> Arun Raj was selected to compose the music for this film, marking his first collaboration between Magizh Tirumeni and Arun Vijay. Gopinath and [[N. B. Srikanth]] were signed on to be the film's cinematographer and editor.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/apr/17/arun-vijays-next-based-on-real-life-incident-1594534.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/arun-vijay-magizh-thirumeni-film-gets-a-new-composer/articleshow/59677327.cms</ref> [[FEFSI Vijayan]] and [[Meera Krishnan]] were also cast in the film before the film entered production in June 2017.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/chennai/aruns-film-with-magizh-is-titled-thadam/articleshow/59105461.cms</ref><ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/fefsi-vijayan-to-play-the-lead-villain-in-arun-vijay-magizh-tirumeni-film-tamil-news-185645.html</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThis film's soundtrack is composed by Arun Raj making his debut as a music director. Lyrics are written by Arun Raj, [[Madhan Karky]], [[Thamarai]], and [[Magizh Thirumeni]]\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Inayae\n| lyrics1 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra1 = [[Sid Sriram]], [[Padmalatha]]\n| length1 = 3:35\n| title2 = Tappu Thanda\n| lyrics2 = [[Eknath]]\n| extra2 = V. M. Mahalingam, Arun Raj, Rohit Sridhar\n| length2 = 3:40\n| title3 = Vidhi Nadhiyae\n| lyrics3 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra3 = [[L. V. Revanth]]\n| length3 = 3:20\n| title4 = Thadam Theme\n| lyrics4 = Arun Raj\n| extra4 = Arun Raj\n| length4 = 2:00\n| title5 = Vidhi Nadhiyae (reprise)\n| lyrics5 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra5 = Arun Raj\n| length5 = 3:28\n| total length = 16:03\n}}\n\n==Box Office==\nThadam grossed Rs 2.3 cr in its third weekend, taking its estimated cumulative gross in Tamil Nadu to Rs 16.4 cr at the end of 20 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/arun-vijays-thadam-continues-blockbuster-run-in-tamil-nadu-ispade-rajavum-idhaya-raniyum-struggles-at-box-office-6305951.html|title=Arun Vijay's Thadam continues blockbuster run in Tamil Nadu; Ispade Rajavum Idhaya Raniyum struggles at box-office|website=Firstpost|access-date=2019-10-10|date=2019-03-22}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|7822438}}\n\n{{Magizh Thirumeni}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s crime action films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime action films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Twins in Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Magizh Thirumeni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 film directed by Magizh Thirumeni}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Thadam\n| image          = Thadam poster.jpg\n| alt            = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Magizh Thirumeni]]\n| producer       = Inder Kumar\n| writer         = Magizh Thirumeni\n| starring       = [[Arun Vijay]]<br>[[Tanya Hope]]<br>[[Smruthi Venkat]]<br>[[Vidya Pradeep]]\n| music          = Arun Raj\n| cinematography = Gopinath\n| editing        = [[N. B. Srikanth]]\n| studio         = Redhan \u2013 The Cinema People\n| distributor    = Screen Scene Media Entertainment \n| released       = 1 March 2019\n| runtime        = 138 Minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RedhanCinemas/status/1029615212318486528|title=#Redhan on Twitter: \"With utmost pleasure and gratitude presenting you the #censor #certificate for #Thadam #releasingsoon #watchout4Thadam #RedhanProduction2\"|website=[[Twitter]]|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n| gross          = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n}}\n\n'''''Thadam''''' ({{Literal translation|Path}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action thriller film]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/south-gossip/article/thadam-movie-review-audience-is-in-awe-of-the-action-thriller-starring-arun-vijay-read-tweets/374775|title=Thadam Movie Review: Audience is in awe of the action thriller starring Arun Vijay - read tweets|website=[[Times Now]]|date=1 March 2019}}</ref> written and directed by [[Magizh Thirumeni]] and produced by Inder Kumar. The film stars [[Arun Vijay]] in a [[double role]] along with [[Tanya Hope]], [[Smruthi Venkat]], and [[Vidya Pradeep]] in the lead roles. The music was composed by Arun Raj, with cinematography done by Gopinath and editing by [[N. B. Srikanth]]. ''Thadam'' marks the Tamil debut of Hope and the film debut of Venkat.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/jun/12/arun-vijays-next-confirmed-to-have-three-heroines-1615878.html</ref> \n\nThe film revolves around two lookalike men, Ezhil and Kavin. While Ezhil is a construction businessman leading a peaceful life, Kavin is a thief who spends most of time gambling and conning. One night, when both are having a hard time, one of them breaks into a man's house and brutally kills him. When the investigation begins, an evidence leads to the cops capturing Ezhil, before they also come across Kavin and find themselves looking for the real murderer among the two as they dig deeper into the investigation.\n\n''Thadam'' was released theatrically on 1 March 2019, opening to praise for Arun Vijay's performance and the writing of the title's logo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/thadam-movie-review-ratings-critics-give-thumbs-arun-vijay-starrer-792894|title=Thadam movie review and ratings: Critics give thumbs up for Arun Vijay-starrer|website=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=28 February 2019}}</ref> It was commercially successful, becoming one of the highest-grossing films of the year in Tamil Nadu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/regional/thadam-one-of-the-top-4-grossers-in-tamil-nadu-this-year-345259.htm|title=Thadam one of the top 4 grossers in Tamil Nadu this year|website=[[In.com]]|accessdate=17 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/pichaikaran-to-thadam-five-blockbuster-tamil-films-which-were-released-in-the-month-of-march/photostory/74794151.cms?picid=74794153|title='Pichaikaran' to 'Thadam': Five blockbuster Tamil films which were released in the month of March|website=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=24 March 2020|quote='Thadam' was an action thriller which was written and directed by Magizh Thirumeni. Arun Vijay played a dual role in the film along with Tanya Hope, Smruthi Venkat and Vidya Pradeep in main roles. The film turned out to be one of the highest-grossing films of the year in Tamil Nadu.}}</ref> The film is being remade in Telugu as ''[[Red (2020 film)|Red]]'' with [[Ram Pothineni]] in the lead role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/oct/28/thadam-telugu-remake-titled-red-15172.html|title=Thadam Telugu remake titled Red|website=[[Cinema Express]]|accessdate=28 October 2019}}</ref> A [[Hindi]]-language remake with [[Sidharth Malhotra]] is also in works.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/sidharth-malhotra-to-star-in-hindi-remake-of-tamil-action-thriller-thadam-film-to-release-on-20-november-8116611.html|title=Sidharth Malhotra to star in Hindi remake of Tamil action thriller Thadam; film to release on 20 November|website=[[Firstpost]]|accessdate=4 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/thadam-be-remade-hindi-siddharth-malhotra-117344|title='Thadam' to be remade in Hindi with Siddharth Malhotra?|website=[[The News Minute]]|accessdate=1 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nEzhil is a construction businessman while his lookalike Kavin is a gambling thief who deceives people along with his sidekick Suruli. A girl named Ananthi loves Kavin, unaware of his real identity. One day, Kavin tries to help Suruli pay his debt by extracting money from Ananthi through lies, but she helps him in spite of knowing the truth. After taking the money, Kavin is enraged and so is Ezhil after a party. That night, one of them breaks into the house of a young man named Akash and beats him to death. The next day, Kavin frees Suruli by paying his debt and wins Ananthi's trust by returning her money and telling her the truth. However, as the investigation of Akash's murder proceeds, a selfie clicked by a couple nearby is found with either of Ezhil or Kavin in it. Both Ezhil and Kavin are brought in and investigated without their knowledge of each other's existence. Gopalakrishnan, an inspector who shares an old rivalry with Ezhil, tortures him. Ezhil reveals his car broke down, and a call taxi driver helped him. Kavin, on the other hand, cites various laws to escape torture. Sub-inspector Malarvizhi is assigned to solve the case. She reaches out to Akash's friend and shows him the photograph of Ezhil/Kavin but he refuses to recognize him. She also questions Suruli and tells him not to leave city without permission, but he secretly escapes.\n\nMalarvizhi then learns of the rivalry between Ezhil and Gopalakrishnan. Ezhil helped the latter's daughter elope with her lover, much against her father's wishes. She gets a call from a forensic expert who informs her about a hair sample recovered from the crime scene and how it doesn't match anyone else in Akash's home. At the police station, a restless Ezhil uses an opportunity to escape, but is interrupted by Kavin. The two violently fight, hurting everyone and destroying the station in the process. It is then revealed they're both identical twins after their DNA is found identical. Both Ezhil and Kavin confess about the same; they parted ways when their parents divorced. Kavin went with his mother who used to gamble a lot and one day tried to convince him that she'd give up gambling, but instead committed suicide. Kavin was then taken in by his father but often got into brawls with him and Ezhil. Growing up, Kavin became interested in studying the law but left studies due to his lack of college ethics. One day, when Kavin came home and left in front of Ezhil whose ring for Deepika went missing, Ezhil reported him to the police. The police beat up Kavin who himself told Ezhil to look for the ring in the drawer. Ezhil realized his mistake but Kavin, who came home for a photo of their mother, vowed to seek revenge. \n\nOn the other hand, Gopalakrishnan still wants to frame Ezhil but the call taxi driver who helped Ezhil reveals he was really stuck on the night of murder. Since it also gets proved that Kavin paid Suruli's debt with gambling money he won after playing all night, the case further complicates. The brothers are presented before the court, where the judge acquits both of them in order to prevent the innocent one from suffering the consequences. A disappointed Malazvizhi later calls Akash's friend to inquire about the girl he was infatuated to. Learning it was Deepika, she is shocked. It is finally revealed that Ezhil murdered Akash for drugging, kidnapping and raping Deepika to death, while Kavin found out about akash's death and helped Ezhil by getting arrested and complicating the case. \n\nKavin meets with Ezhil in the highways and says that Malarvizhi can't reopen the case because she created a fake witness to help Ezhil, and could herself get into trouble. Kavin further reveals that he has forever lost all interest in gambling and he's going to marry Ananthi soon. Ezhil hands him over a photograph of them with their mother and tells him he is going to Mumbai, and later to Copenhagen, never to return. Ezhil has sold all of his property in India, and gives 50% share to Kavin as a tribute. A month later, Kavin marries Ananthi, and realises that his lack of trust in his mother, prompted her to kill herself. At the end, one of the investigating officers claims in a documentary shooting that such a case never happened in the past, before someone tells him similar cases did occur in America and some such cases are listed on the screen.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Arun Vijay]] in a dual role as Ezhil and Kavin\n*[[Tanya Hope]] as Deepika, Ezhil's love interest\n*[[Smruthi Venkat]] as Ananthi, an innocent women and Kavin's one-sided lover \n*[[Vidya Pradeep]] as Sub-Inspector Malarvizhi\n*[[Sonia Aggarwal]] as Ezhil and Kavin's mother\n*[[FEFSI Vijayan]] as Inspector M. Gopalakrishnan\n*Yesakkiappan as Aakash\n*[[Yogi Babu]] as Suruli\n*[[George Maryan|George]] as Police Constable Dhanasekar \n*[[Meera Krishnan]] as Chechi \n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nIn March 2017, [[Arun Vijay]] revealed that he would next work on a film directed by [[Magizh Thirumeni]], which marks the second film for the duo after ''[[Thadaiyara Thaakka]]'' (2012).<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/yet-another-thriller-for-arun-vijay/articleshow/57631341.cms</ref> Produced by Inder Kumar, the film was launched in April 2017 at Chennai.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/arun-vijay-magizh-thirumeni-untitled-movie-tamil-movie-preview-21475</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/yet-another-thriller-for-arun-vijay/articleshow/57631341.cms</ref> Arun Vijay was reported to be playing a double role, while the film would be based on a real life story.<ref>http://www.sify.com/movies/arun-vijay-to-play-dual-role-in-the-film-with-magizh-thirumeni-news-tnpl-reejnugfihhdg.html</ref> The film has three heroines, Tanya Hope, Vidya Pradeep and Smruthi Venkat.<ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/tanya-hope-soori-and-vidya-pradeep-the-three-heroines-in-arun-vijay-magizh-tirumeni-thadam-tamil-news-191506</ref> Arun Raj was selected to compose the music for this film, marking his first collaboration between Magizh Tirumeni and Arun Vijay. Gopinath and [[N. B. Srikanth]] were signed on to be the film's cinematographer and editor.<ref>http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2017/apr/17/arun-vijays-next-based-on-real-life-incident-1594534.html</ref><ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/arun-vijay-magizh-thirumeni-film-gets-a-new-composer/articleshow/59677327.cms</ref> [[FEFSI Vijayan]] and [[Meera Krishnan]] were also cast in the film before the film entered production in June 2017.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/chennai/aruns-film-with-magizh-is-titled-thadam/articleshow/59105461.cms</ref><ref>https://www.indiaglitz.com/fefsi-vijayan-to-play-the-lead-villain-in-arun-vijay-magizh-tirumeni-film-tamil-news-185645.html</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThis film's soundtrack is composed by Arun Raj making his debut as a music director. Lyrics are written by Arun Raj, [[Madhan Karky]], [[Thamarai]], and [[Magizh Thirumeni]]\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Inayae\n| lyrics1 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra1 = [[Sid Sriram]], [[Padmalatha]]\n| length1 = 3:35\n| title2 = Tappu Thanda\n| lyrics2 = [[Eknath]]\n| extra2 = V. M. Mahalingam, Arun Raj, Rohit Sridhar\n| length2 = 3:40\n| title3 = Vidhi Nadhiyae\n| lyrics3 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra3 = [[L. V. Revanth]]\n| length3 = 3:20\n| title4 = Thadam Theme\n| lyrics4 = Arun Raj\n| extra4 = Arun Raj\n| length4 = 2:00\n| title5 = Vidhi Nadhiyae (reprise)\n| lyrics5 = [[Madhan Karky]]\n| extra5 = Arun Raj\n| length5 = 3:28\n| total length = 16:03\n}}\n\n==Box Office==\nThadam grossed Rs 2.3 cr in its third weekend, taking its estimated cumulative gross in Tamil Nadu to Rs 16.4 cr at the end of 20 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/arun-vijays-thadam-continues-blockbuster-run-in-tamil-nadu-ispade-rajavum-idhaya-raniyum-struggles-at-box-office-6305951.html|title=Arun Vijay's Thadam continues blockbuster run in Tamil Nadu; Ispade Rajavum Idhaya Raniyum struggles at box-office|website=Firstpost|access-date=2019-10-10|date=2019-03-22}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|7822438}}\n\n{{Magizh Thirumeni}}\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s crime action films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime action films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Twins in Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Magizh Thirumeni]]\n", "name_user": "Fahim bin mourshed", "label": "safe", "comment": "It was being remade into bengali as ''Red\" with shakib khan probably play the lead role slated to release in july 2020", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thadam"}
{"title_page": "Pafos FC", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Pafos FC\n| image = \n| fullname = Pafos Football Club\n| founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2014|6|10}}\n| ground = [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium|Stelios Kyriakides]], [[Paphos]]\n| capacity = 8,500<ref>https://cyprussports.org/gr/sport-facilities/pafos/pafiako-stadium.html</ref>\n| manager = [[Cameron Toshack]] {{flag|Wales}}\n| league = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos}}\n| season = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos2}}\n| position = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos3}}\n| current = \n| pattern_la1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_b1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_ra1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_sh1 = _macronfootballblacklogo2\n| pattern_so1 = \n| leftarm1 = FFFFFF\n| body1 = FFFFFF\n| rightarm1 = FFFFFF\n| shorts1 = 318CE7\n| socks1 = 318CE7\n| pattern_la2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_b2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_ra2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_sh2 = _macronfootballwhitelogo\n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFFFFF\n| body2 = FFFFFF\n| rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n| shorts2 = 555555\n| socks2 = 555555\n| website = https://pafosfc.com.cy/\n}}\n'''Pafos FC''' ({{lang-el|\u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03c2 FC}}) is a Cypriot [[association football|football]] team based in [[Paphos]]. The club was formed in 2014 after the merger of the biggest teams of Paphos district, based on the historical teams of [[APOP Paphos FC|APOP]] and [[Evagoras Paphos|Evagoras]]. Their home stadium is [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium]] and they are currently competing in the [[Cypriot First Division]].\n\n==History==\nPafos FC is a \"product\" of a form of merger between the strongest football forces of the Province of Paphos. The Pafos FC Association represents Paphian football and sports throughout Cyprus through the football team and the Football Academy, which has hosts hundreds of young athletes. The emblem of Pafos FC includes the name of the Club and Town  in which the figure of the Eternal Adolescent Hero [[Evagoras Pallikarides]] is integrated. The shape and colors of the emblem (white, blue and gold) refer to the historical clubs of APOP and AEK Kouklia. The emblem was renewed during the period 2018-19, making the figure of the hero Evagoras Pallikarides more visible.\n\nOn June 10, 2014, in the historic building of the [[AEP Paphos FC]], hosted the first gathering of the friends of the merged team, in the presence of politicians, active and veteran football players of Paphos and hundreds of fans. The first president of the team was Christakis Kaizer, who was the president of AEK Kouklia and one of the main people of the effort to create the new team together with the then six-member managing committee of AEP, consisting of pure friends of the Paphian team, who kept it alive until the end of the then season, along with the then coaches, young players and executives and players of the Academy, under adverse economic conditions.\n\nAs an official home stadium for its obligations in the championship of the first division, the team uses [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium]] (Paphiako Stadium).\n\nThe purpose of the Club is to promote noble rivalry, \" fair play \" and culture both through sports activities and through numerous cultural and educational events, visits to schools and educational institutions in Paphos. For the past two years, the team has been projecting a picture of renewal and full professionalism in all departments and levels. An important event is the complete renovation of the training center to the standards of European clubs.\n\nThe team's first coach was [[Radmilo Ivan\u010devi\u0107]], who served as AEP Paphos coach in the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pafosfc.com.cy/index.php/press-release/item/17-2014-07-03-19-25-33 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808050159/http://www.pafosfc.com.cy/index.php/press-release/item/17-2014-07-03-19-25-33 |url-status=dead |archive-date=8 August 2014 |script-title=el:\u03a3\u03a5\u039c\u03a6\u03a9\u039d\u0399\u0391 \u039c\u0395 \u03a1\u0391\u03a4\u039c\u0399\u039b\u039f \u0399\u0392\u0391\u039d\u03a4\u03a3\u0395\u0392\u0399\u03a4\u03a3 |publisher=pafosfc.com.cy |language=Greek |date=3 July 2014 |accessdate=1 August 2014 }}</ref> Pafos FC competed in the 2014\u201315 [[Cypriot Second Division]], in their first season as a club.\n\nThe new team participated in the Division B championship 2014-15. The first match in Club's new history was against [[Enosis Neon Paralimni FC]], at the Municipal Stadium of Geroskipou which was the first Home stadium of the team. At the end of the period the team achieved the second place and was promoted to the first division. In 2015-16 season, in the first participation of Pafos FC in the firts division, the team finished in 12th place and was relegated. First victory and the team's first overall victory in the first division came on September 12, 2015 in the third game of the league when Pafos FC defeated [[Aris Limassol FC]] 3-0 at home.\n\nIn 2016-17 season, the team finished second in second division championship and was promoted to the First Division. In 2017-18 season, Pafos FC remained in the top division, finishing in tenth place under the new the management of the team by the Russian investor Sergey Lomakin and British Roman Dubov, who raised the level of the team through resounding transfers, changes in the structure of the team, strengthening the operation of the Academy and thriugh the renovation of the Training Center of PAFOS FC and its transformation into one of the most modern and well-equipped in Cyprus.\n\n==Badge and colors==\nThe logo of Pafos FC is a variation of [[AEP Paphos F.C.|AEP Paphos]]'s logo and a refresh of Pafos FC first logo, including the name of the team and town and the classic figure of the hero [[Evagoras Pallikaridis]]. The logo also includes the team's colors, the blue, white and gold.<ref>{{Cite web|url =http://sentragoal.philenews.com/article.asp?catid=19171&subid=2&pubid=129747729|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140808044924/http://sentragoal.philenews.com/article.asp?catid=19171&subid=2&pubid=129747729|url-status =dead|archive-date =8 August 2014|title =\u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03c2 FC: \u039c\u03b5 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03b3\u03c9\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf \u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03bb\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c3\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5|date =3 June 2014|accessdate =1 August 2014|publisher =sentragoal.philenews.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://protathlima.com/index.php?id=63174|title =\u0394\u03b5\u03af\u03c4\u03b5 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ad\u03bc\u03b2\u03bb\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03c2 F.C!|date =7 June 2014|accessdate =1 August 2014|publisher =protathlima.com}}</ref> The emblem was renewed during the period 2018-19, making the figure of the hero Evagoras Pallikarides more visible.\n\n<br />\n\n===Shirt sponsors and manufacturers===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; \"\n|-\n! Period\n! Kit manufacturer\n! Shirt sponsor\n|-\n| 2017\u20132019\n| [[Jako]]\n| rowspan=2|  [[KORANTINA HOMES]]\n|-\n| 2019\u2013\n| Macron\n|}\n\n==Current squad==\n{{updated|8 January 2020}}<ref>https://pafosfc.com.cy/our-team</ref>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=1|nat=UKR|pos=GK|name=[[Artur Rudko]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=3|nat=URU|pos=DF|name=[[Joaqu\u00edn Varela (footballer, born 1998)|Joaqu\u00edn Varela]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=5|nat=CYP|pos=DF|name=Kyriakos Antoniou}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=6|nat=NGR|pos=MF|name=[[Stephen Sunday|Sunny]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=7|nat=USA|pos=MF|name=[[Danny Williams (soccer, born 1989)|Danny Williams]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=8|nat=SLO|pos=DF|name=[[Matija \u0160irok]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=FRA|pos=FW|name=[[K\u00e9vin B\u00e9rigaud]]|other=}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=11|nat=CYP|pos=FW|name=[[Alex Konstantinou]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=12|nat=CYP|pos=GK|name=Evgenios Petrou}}\n{{Fs player|no=13|nat=HAI|pos=DF|name=[[Kevin Lafrance]]|other=on loan from [[APOEL FC|APOEL]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=14|nat=CYP|pos=MF|name=[[Gerasimos Fylaktou]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=15|nat=GRE|pos=DF|name=[[Giorgos Valerianos]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=16|nat=NOR|pos=MF|name=[[Abdisalam Ibrahim]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=17|nat=SWE|pos=MF|name=[[Nahir Besara]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=18|nat=FRA|pos=DF|name=[[Micka\u00ebl Panos]]}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|nat=JPN|pos=MF|name=[[Cy Goddard]]|other=on loan from [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=22|nat=CYP|pos=DF|name=[[Andreas Panayiotou Filiotis|Andreas Panagiotou]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[captain (association football)|Captain]]|no=23|nat=FIN|pos=DF|name=[[Paulus Arajuuri]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=24|nat=FIN|pos=MF|name=[[Onni Valakari]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=26|nat=MLI|pos=MF|name=[[Bakary Sako]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=28|nat=ANG|pos=FW|name=[[V\u00e1 (footballer)|V\u00e1]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[captain (association football)|Vice-captain]]|no=31|nat=CZE|pos=MF|name=[[Zden\u011bk Folprecht (footballer)|Zden\u011bk Folprecht]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=32|nat=ARG|pos=FW|name=[[Marcelo Torres]]|other=on loan from [[Boca Juniors]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=[[captain (association football)|Vice-captain]]|no=42|nat=ENG|pos=MF|name=[[Jason Puncheon]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=52|nat=LAT|pos=GK|name=[[Reinis Reinholds]]|other=on loan from [[A.C. Pisa 1909|Pisa]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=66|nat=RUS|pos=MF|name=[[Pavel Leliukhin]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=77|nat=SVK|pos=FW|name=[[Adam Nemec]]|other=}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=91|nat=CPV|pos=FW|name=[[Jerson Cabral]]}}\n{{Fs player|other=|no=92|nat=LAT|pos=FW|name=[[Deniss Rakels]]}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n===Out on loan===\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=70|nat=COL|pos=MF|name=[[Brayan Edinson Angulo Mosquera|Brayan Angulo]]|other= at [[Riga FC|Riga]]}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n\n''For recent transfers, see [[List of Cypriot football transfers winter 2019\u201320]].''\n\n==Current staff==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"| Senior Management\n|-\n|align=left|CEO\n|align=left|{{flagicon|LVA}} [[Pavel Gognidze]]\n|-\n|align=left|Sporting Director\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jeremy Steele]]\n|-\n|Head Scouter\n|{{flagicon|Russia}} Andrey Grushin\n|-\n|Press Officer\n|{{flagicon|Greece}} Polyvios Paliouras\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Technical staff\n|-\n|align=left|Head Coach\n|align=left|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Cameron Toshack]]\n|-\n|align=left|Assistant Coach\n|align=left|{{flagicon|WAL}} [[Gary Richards (footballer)|Gary Richards]]\n|-\n|align=left|Head of Performance \n|align=left|{{flagicon|WAL}}  [[Richard Buchanan (physiotherapist)|Richard Buchanan]]\n|-\n|align=left|Goalkeeping Coach\n|align=left|{{flagicon|CYP}}  Nikos Constantinides\n|-\n|align=left|Head of Performance Analysis\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}}  Charlie Mitchell\n|-\n|align=left|Strength & Conditioning Coach \n|align=left|{{flagicon|ESP}} Jesus Pinedo\n|-\n|align=left|Analyst\n|align=left|{{flagicon|CYP}} Giorgos Christodoulou \n|-\n|align=left|Head of Medical\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GRE}} Nikos Koundourakis \n|-\n|}\n\n==Managers==\n*{{flagicon|SRB}} [[Radmilo Ivan\u010devi\u0107]] (2014\u20132014)\n*{{flagicon|CYP}} [[Sofoklis Sofokleous]] (2014\u20132015)\n*{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Roca Cases|Jos\u00e9 Manuel Roca]] (2015\u20132015)\n*{{flagicon|CYP}} [[Apostolos Makridis]] (2015\u20132016)\n*{{flagicon|CYP}} [[Dimitris Ioannou]] (2016\u20132017)\n*{{flagicon|SVN}} [[Luka Elsner]] (2017\u20132018)\n*{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Steven Pressley]] (2018)\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[\u017deljko Kopi\u0107]] (2018\u20132019)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{portal|Cyprus|Association football}}\n{{Cypriot First Division}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 2014]]\n[[Category:2014 establishments in Cyprus]]\n[[Category:Pafos FC| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| clubname = Pafos FC\n| image = \n| fullname = Pafos Football Club\n| founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2014|6|10}}\n| ground = [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium|Stelios Kyriakides]], [[Paphos]]\n| capacity = 8,500<ref>https://cyprussports.org/gr/sport-facilities/pafos/pafiako-stadium.html</ref>\n| manager = [[Cameron Toshack]] {{flag|Wales}}\n| league = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos}}\n| season = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos2}}\n| position = {{Cypriot football updater|Pafos3}}\n| current = \n| pattern_la1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_b1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_ra1 = _shelbourne17a\n| pattern_sh1 = _macronfootballblacklogo2\n| pattern_so1 = \n| leftarm1 = FFFFFF\n| body1 = FFFFFF\n| rightarm1 = FFFFFF\n| shorts1 = 318CE7\n| socks1 = 318CE7\n| pattern_la2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_b2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_ra2 = _dbucaresti1718a\n| pattern_sh2 = _macronfootballwhitelogo\n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2 = FFFFFF\n| body2 = FFFFFF\n| rightarm2 = FFFFFF\n| shorts2 = 555555\n| socks2 = 555555\n| website = https://pafosfc.com.cy/\n}}\n'''Pafos FC''' ({{lang-el|\u03a0\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03c2 FC}}) is a Cypriot [[association football|football]] team based in [[Paphos]]. The club was formed in 2014 after the merger of the biggest teams of Paphos district, based on the historical teams of [[APOP Paphos FC|APOP]] and [[Evagoras Paphos|Evagoras]]. Their home stadium is [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium]] and they are currently competing in the [[Cypriot First Division]].\n\n==History==\nPafos FC is a \"product\" of a form of merger between the strongest football forces of the Province of Paphos. The Pafos FC Association represents Paphian football and sports throughout Cyprus through the football team and the Football Academy, which has hosts hundreds of young athletes. The emblem of Pafos FC includes the name of the Club and Town  in which the figure of the Eternal Adolescent Hero [[Evagoras Pallikarides]] is integrated. The shape and colors of the emblem (white, blue and gold) refer to the historical clubs of APOP and AEK Kouklia. The emblem was renewed during the period 2018-19, making the figure of the hero Evagoras Pallikarides more visible.\n\nOn June 10, 2014, in the historic building of the [[AEP Paphos FC]], hosted the first gathering of the friends of the merged team, in the presence of politicians, active and veteran football players of Paphos and hundreds of fans. The first president of the team was Christakis Kaizer, who was the president of AEK Kouklia and one of the main people of the effort to create the new team together with the then six-member managing committee of AEP, consisting of pure friends of the Paphian team, who kept it alive until the end of the then season, along with the then coaches, young players and executives and players of the Academy, under adverse economic conditions.\n\nAs an official home stadium for its obligations in the championship of the first division, the team uses [[Stelios Kyriakides Stadium]] (Paphiako Stadium).\n\nThe purpose of the Club is to promote noble rivalry, \" fair play \" and culture both through sports activities and through numerous cultural and educational events, visits to schools and educational institutions in Paphos. For the past two years, the team has been projecting a picture of renewal and full professionalism in all departments and levels. An important event is the complete renovation of the training center to the standards of European clubs.\n\nThe team's first coach was [[Radmilo Ivan\u010devi\u0107]], who served as AEP Paphos coach in the past.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pafosfc.com.cy/index.php/press-release/item/17-2014-07-03-19-25-33 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808050159/http://www.pafosfc.com.cy/index.php/press-release/item/17-2014-07-03-19-25-33 |url-status=dead |archive-date=8 August 2014 |script-title=el:\u03a3\u03a5\u039c\u03a6\u03a9\u039d\u0399\u0391 \u039c\u0395 \u03a1\u0391\u03a4\u039c\u0399\u039b\u039f \u0399\u0392\u0391\u039d\u03a4\u03a3\u0395\u0392\u0399\u03a4\u03a3 |publisher=pafosfc.com.cy |language=Greek |date=3 July 2014 |accessdate=1 August 2014 }}</ref> Pafos FC competed in the 2014\u201315 [[Cypriot Second Division]], in their first season as a club.\n\nThe new team participated in the Division B championship 2014-15. The first match in Club's new history was against [[Enosis Neon Paralimni FC]], at the Municipal Stadium of Geroskipou which was the first Home stadium of the team. At the end of the period the team achieved the second place and was promoted to the first division. In 2015-16 season, in the first participation of Pafos FC in the firts division, the team finished in 12th place and was relegated. First victory and the team's first overall victory in the first division came on September 12, 2015 in the third game of the league when Pafos FC defeated [[Aris Limassol FC]] 3-0 at home.\n\nIn 2016-17 season, the team finished second in second division championship and was promoted to the First Division. In 2017-18 season, Pafos FC remained in the top division, finishing in tenth place under the new the management of the team by the Russian investor Sergey Lomakin and British Roman Dubov, who raised the level of the team through resounding transfers, changes in the structure of the team, strengthening the operation of the Academy and thriugh the renovation of the Training Center of PAFOS FC and its transformation into one of the most modern and well-equipped in Cyprus.\n\n==Badge and colors==\nThe logo of Pafos FC is a variation of [[AEP Paphos F.C.|AEP Paphos]]'s logo and a refresh of Pafos FC first logo, including the name of the team and town and the classic figure of the hero [[Evagoras Pallikaridis]]. The logo also includes the team's colors, the blue, white and gold.<ref>{{Cite web|url =http://sentragoal.philenews.com/article.asp?catid=19171&subid=2&pubid=129747729|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140808044924/http://sentragoal.philenews.com/artic