lever Directors Award<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/hul-allcargo-top-honchos-win-the-last-leg-of-et-golf/articleshow/5635162.cms?from=mdr|title=HUL, Allcargo top honchos win the last leg of ET golf|date=2010-03-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-07-08}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Rudratej}}\n[[Category:1970s births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:BMW people]]\n[[Category:Institute of Management Technology, Ghaziabad alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School Advanced Management Program attendees]]\n", "name_user": "49.207.86.203", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eEarly life and education)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rudratej_Singh"}
{"title_page": "R. Rathnavelu", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian cinematographer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n\n'''R. Rathnavelu''' is an Indian cinematographer who has worked predominantly in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films. His work in films such as ''[[Nandha]]'', ''[[Vaaranam Aayiram]]'', ''[[Enthiran]]'', ''[[Rangasthalam]]'', ''[[Sye Raa Narasimha Reddy]]'', ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]''\nhas gained recognition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-12-06/news-interviews/28090825_1_endhiran-film-camera-arri|title=I adore Rajinikanth: Rathnavelu|work=The Times of India}}</ref> He has garnered three [[Filmfare Awards South]], the Vijay Awards, the Tamil Nadu State Film Award, two [[ South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award]] and the prestigious Kalaimamani Award bestowed by the Tamil nadu state government for his work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/celeb/interview/rathnavelu.html|title=Interview with R. Rathnavelu - Telugu cinema cinematographer|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/Khaidi-No.150-Chiranjeevi-returns-in-style/article17022568.ece|title=Khaidi No.150: Chiranjeevi returns in style|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRathnavelu a member of the Indian Society of Cinematographers and graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Physics and completed the three year Diploma in Film Technology in cinematography from the [[M.G.R. Government Film and Television Training Institute]]. He went on to assist Cinematographer Rajeev Menon for the Mani Rathnam movie Bombay .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/light-camera-and-a-lens-to-top-it-all/article5598196.ece|title=Light, camera and a lens to top it all|first=Suresh|last=Krishnamoorthy|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1997 || ''[[Aravindhan]]'' || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[Sandhippoma]]'' || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|- \n| 1999 || ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Nandha]]'' || Tamil || [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer - South]]<br />[[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Cinematographer]]\n|-\n| 2002|| ''[[Bagavathi]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Jayam (2003 film)|Jayam]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Thirumalai]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Arya (2004 film)|Arya]]'' || Telugu || \n|- \n| 2004 || ''[[Perazhagan]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[Maayavi]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[February 14 (film)|February 14]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2006|| ''[[Cyanide (2006 film)|Cyanide]]'' || Kannada || \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Jagadam]]'' || Telugu || \n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Gaalipata]]'' || Kannada ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Vaaranam Aayiram]]'' || Tamil || Nominated\u2014[[Vijay Award for Best Cinematographer]] \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Enthiran]]'' || Tamil || [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer - South]]<br />\n[[Vijay Award for Best Cinematographer]]\n|-\n\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[David (2013 Tamil film)|David]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[David (2013 Hindi film)|David]]'' || [[Hindi]] || \n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Haridas (2013 film)|Haridas]]'' || Tamil|| \n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[1: Nenokkadine]]'' || Telugu || Won [[4th South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award for Best Cinematography - Telugu]]\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Lingaa]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2015 || ''[[Kumari 21F]]'' || Telugu ||\n|-\n| 2016 || ''[[Brahmotsavam (film)|Bramhotsavam]]'' || Telugu ||\n|-\n| 2017 || ''[[Khaidi No. 150]]'' || Telugu ||\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[Rangasthalam]]'' || Telugu ||  Won [[8th South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award for Best Cinematography - Telugu]] <br /> [[ Filmfare Award ]] <br /> [[ Sakshi Award ]] <br /> [[Zee TV Award]] <br /> [[ Dada Saheb Phalke Award ]]\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Sye Raa Narasimha Reddy]]'' || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]'' || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||\n|-\n| 2021 || ''[[Indian 2]]'' || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|}v\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20140112015816/http://www.doprandy.com/ Official Website]\n* {{IMDb name|id=nm1394723}}\n\n{{Tamil Nadu State Film Award Best Cinematography}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rathnavelu, R.}}\n[[Category:Artists from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Cinematographers from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Telugu film cinematographers]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards South winners]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:Tamil Nadu State Film Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Film and Television Institute of Tamil Nadu alumni]]\n[[Category:Hindi film cinematographers]]\n[[Category:Kannada film cinematographers]]\n[[Category:Tamil film cinematographers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian cinematographer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}}\n\n'''R. Rathnavelu''' is an Indian cinematographer who has worked predominantly in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] films. His work in films such as ''[[Nandha]]'', ''[[Vaaranam Aayiram]]'', ''[[Enthiran]]'', ''[[Rangasthalam ]]'', ''[[Sye Raa Narasimha Reddy]]'', ''[[Sarileru Neekevvaru]]''\nhas gained recognition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-12-06/news-interviews/28090825_1_endhiran-film-camera-arri|title=I adore Rajinikanth: Rathnavelu|work=The Times of India}}</ref> He has garnered three [[Filmfare Awards South]], the Vijay Awards, the Tamil Nadu State Film Award, two [[ South Indian International Movie Awards|SIIMA Award]] and the prestigious Kalaimamani Award bestowed by the Tamil nadu state government for his work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/celeb/interview/rathnavelu.html|title=Interview with R. Rathnavelu - Telugu cinema cinematographer|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/Khaidi-No.150-Chiranjeevi-returns-in-style/article17022568.ece|title=Khaidi No.150: Chiranjeevi returns in style|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRathnavelu a member of the Indian Society of Cinematographers and graduated with a Bachelor of Science degree in Physics and completed the three year Diploma in Film Technology in cinematography from the [[M.G.R. Government Film and Television Training Institute]]. He went on to assist Cinematographer Rajeev Menon for the Mani Rathnam movie Bombay .<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/light-camera-and-a-lens-to-top-it-all/article5598196.ece|title=Light, camera and a lens to top it all|first=Suresh|last=Krishnamoorthy|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Film !! Language !! Notes\n|-\n|-\n| 1997 || ''[[Aravindhan]]'' || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|-\n| 1998 || ''[[Sandhippoma]]'' || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|- \n| 1999 || ''[[Sethu (film)|Sethu]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[Nandha]]'' || Tamil || [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer - South]]<br />[[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Cinematographer]]\n|-\n| 2002|| ''[[Bagavathi]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Jayam (2003 film)|Jayam]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Thirumalai]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Arya (2004 film)|Arya]]'' || Telugu || \n|- \n| 2004 || ''[[Perazhagan]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[Maayavi]]'' || Tamil ||\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[February 14 (film)|February 14]]'' || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2006|| ''[[Cyanide (2006 film)|Cyanide]]'' || Kannada || \n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Jagadam]]'' || Telugu || \n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Gaalipata]]'' || Kannada ||\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Vaaranam Aayiram]]'' || Tamil || Nominated\u2014[[Vijay Award for Best Cinematographer]] \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Enthiran]]'' || Tamil || [[Filmfare Aw